Ellina Mhlanga Sports Reporter&#8212;AS the country prepares to host the 2017 CANA Zone IV Swimming and Waterpolo Championships, the Zimbabwe Aquatic Union are confident they are on the right track. Most of their swimmers at the ongoing African Union Sports Council Region Five Under-20 Youth Games are posting good results. The regional championships from February 16 to 19 in Bulawayo. ZAU president, Mary Kloppers, reckons results from AUSC Region Five Games are encouraging ahead of next year s event.